00:41:39.990 --> 00:41:43.330
circuit here. You can put more than
one electrical signal through an

00:41:43.330 --> 00:41:46.660
item. So, let's put a second
circuit through here.

00:41:46.660 --> 00:42:06.253
And, this circuit is a little
heater circuit.

00:41:30.000 --> 00:41:35.000
And, all it does is it makes this
cathode filament through joule

00:41:35.000 --> 00:41:40.000
heating, raise its temperature.
And that makes the electrons less

00:41:40.000 --> 00:41:45.000
tightly bound,
so it's easier to boil them off.

00:41:45.000 --> 00:41:50.000
So, the hot cathode, by raising
temperature, reduces binding of the

00:41:50.000 --> 00:41:55.000
electrons. And,
you're trying to get rid of them.

00:41:55.000 --> 00:42:00.000
The third thing he did was water
cooling.

00:42:00.000 --> 00:42:04.000
You've got all of these electrons.
They've zoomed across at an

00:42:04.000 --> 00:42:08.000
acceleration voltage of 30,
40, 50,000 volts. They're crash,

00:42:08.000 --> 00:42:12.000
crash, crash, crash, hitting that
copper or molybdenum anode.

00:42:12.000 --> 00:42:16.000
Where is that kinetic energy going?
Some of it's going into light, and

00:42:16.000 --> 00:42:20.000
some of it's going into heat.
And, the temperature of the anode

00:42:20.000 --> 00:42:24.000
is rising to the point where you
could melt this.

00:42:24.000 --> 00:42:28.000
So, what Coolidge did is he put the
anode on a hearth, and

00:42:28.000 --> 00:42:52.460
the hearth is copper..
And underneath,

00:42:52.460 --> 00:42:57.380
there's water running through copper
tubing. So, by water cooling,

00:42:57.380 --> 00:43:02.300
he's able to keep the anode cool,
so, dissipate heat, and the second

00:43:02.300 --> 00:43:07.220
thing, remember,
Roentgen used pulse power.

00:43:07.220 --> 00:43:12.150
It was eight times a second: bam,
bam, bam, bam. If you've got water

00:43:12.150 --> 00:43:17.070
cooling, now you can go to
continuous power,

00:43:17.070 --> 00:43:35.873
dissipated heat, and allowed for
continuous current flow.

00:43:02.000 --> 00:43:07.500
If you've got continuous current,
that means you've got continuous

00:43:07.500 --> 00:43:13.000
x-ray emission.
You don't want an x-ray flashbulb.

00:43:13.000 --> 00:43:18.500
You want an x-ray beam. And, the
